data.description: We don't have a genie in a bottle, but we're about to make your wish come true with this Spring Hill pool home! Sitting on an oversized corner lot in a neighborhood with no HOA fees or restrictions, its curb appeal is off the charts. Meticulous landscaping compliments new gutters, new windows, and neat siding; the roof was replaced in December of 2023, and the AC in 2022. The screened front porch is practically made for lazy afternoons in rocking chairs, sipping sweet tea or lemonade. Inside, new skylights and vaulted ceilings add light, airy volume to the space. Vinyl flooring in the main living areas and primary suite is stylish and easy to maintain. The living and dining rooms offer plenty of space for family or visitors to gather, while the spacious family room is ideal for game or movie nights. The galley-style kitchen features a beautiful glass tile backsplash, formica counters, plenty of cabinet space, and a charming eating nook overlooking the pool area. Retire to the primary bedroom at the end of a long day; it offers an ensuite bathroom with a large shower. The remaining three guest bedrooms are sizable, and the closets in all the bedrooms are deep for ample storage. Grab your towels and sunscreen and head through the glass sliders out to the lanai, where there's a lovely covered area to relax in the shade until you're ready to take a dip. The in-ground pool has a new pump, and is surrounded by a safety fence. The whole pool area is enclosed with new screening. A shed out back provides additional room to stow your belongings. You won't need a magic carpet to navigate the streets of Agrabah here - there's an entrance to the Suncoast Parkway minutes away, so access to Tampa is quick and convenient. You'll have two local parks within a 3 mile radius: Veterans Memorial and Anderson Snow, which has a massive sports complex. You're also not far from dining and shopping options. Take advantage of your proximity to the Adventure Coast to explore Florida's natural beauty! Paddle down the river or meet real mermaids at nearby Weeki Wachee Springs State Park. Will you seize this opportunity to get into your dream home - and the lifestyle you crave? Reach out today to set up a private showing!
